%N A378608 Number of maximal chains in the poset of all compositions with weight <= n, ordered by A covers B iff A_i >= B_{i+k} for all i in B and some k >= 0.
%H A378608 Jan Snellman, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/math/0309458">Standard paths in another composition poset</a>, arXiv:math/0309458 [math.CO], 2003.
%F A378608 G.f.: Sum_{k>=0} L_k(t) where L_k(t) = (2*t*L_{k-1}(t) - t^k)/(1 - k*t) with L_0(t) = 1 (see Snellman link). - _John Tyler Rascoe_, Jul 09 2026
%e A378608 a(3) = 6:
%e A378608   () < (1) < (1,1) < (1,1,1),
%e A378608   () < (1) < (1,1) < (1,2),
%e A378608   () < (1) < (1,1) < (2,1),
%e A378608   () < (1) < (2) < (1,2),
%e A378608   () < (1) < (2) < (2,1),
%e A378608   () < (1) < (2) < (3).
%o A378608 (Python)
%o A378608 def mchains(n,k): return # See A378588
%o A378608 def A378608_list(max_n): return mchains(max_n,max_n)
